AbilityScoreFeature.Name: Normal Human Ability Scores
AbilityScoreFeature.Text: Your ability scores each increase by 1.

MultiFeature.Name: Variant Human Traits
MultiFeature.Text: If your campaign uses the optional feat rules from the Player’s Handbook, your Dungeon Master might allow these variant traits, all of which replace the human’s Ability Score Increase trait.

ChoiceFeature.Name: Ability Score Increase
ChoiceFeature.Text: Two different ability scores of your choice increase by 1

SkillProficiencyChoiceFeature.Name: Skills
SkillProficiencyChoiceFeature.Text: You gain proficiency in one skill of your choice.

CollectionChoiceFeature.Name: Feat
CollectionChoiceFeature.Text: You gain one feat of your choice

Feature.Name: Age
Feature.Text: Humans reach adulthood in their late teens and live less than a century.

Feature.Name: Alignment
Feature.Text: Humans tend toward no particular alignment. The best and the worst are found among them.

Feature.Name: Size
Feature.Text: Humans vary widely in height and build, from barely 5 feet to well over 6 feet tall. Regardless of your position in that range, your size is Medium.

SpeedFeature.Name: Speed
SpeedFeature.Text: Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

ChoiceFeature.Name: Languages
ChoiceFeature.Text: You can speak, read, and write Common and one extra language of your choice. Or, if your campaign uses the optional rules for languages found in the previous section, your national origin determines your native language: Itzocan for the Sun Empire, Coalition pidgin for the Brazen Coalition, or Vampire for the Legion of Dusk. You still speak one additional language of your choice, and Common if it exists in your campaign.

LanguageChoiceFeature.Name: Common and one additional language
LanguageChoiceFeature.Text: You can speak, read, and write Common and one extra language of your choice.

LanguageChoiceFeature.Name: Optional rules for language
LanguageChoiceFeature.Text: Your national origin determines your native language: Itzocan for the Sun Empire, Coalition pidgin for the Brazen Coalition, or Vampire for the Legion of Dusk. You still speak one additional language of your choice, and Common if it exists in your campaign.

Race.Name: Human
Race.Description: Humans are found throughout the plane of Ixalan, both in the lands of Torrezon (now controlled by the Legion of Dusk) and in the Sun Empire. The vampires of the Legion of Dusk were once human, and the peasant and servant populations they rule still are. As the Legion of Dusk conquered Torrezon, its forces drove many human populations before them, including those who first formed the Free Cities and later fled across the ocean to form the core of the Brazen Coalition.

Description.Name: Human Traits
Description.Text: The humans of Ixalan use the human traits presented in the Player’s Handbook.
